GoolagScanner::ScanGoogleProviderImplementation of IScanProvider. This one is Google
GoolagScanner::ScanMonitorThis class takes care of multiple, parallel scans. For this, it provides two data-structures, a list for the scans to do, and a queue for scans that finished - with all neccesary accessors to them. Takes care of synchronizing. An own thread, a watcher, handles the transport between the different pipelines. Running scans are encapsulated by an inner class. So it even would be possible to use different scan engines, and or course different scan providers in one parallised scan
GoolagScanner::ScanMonitor::ActiveScanA scan that is running or that has to be run
GoolagScanner::ScannerScanner, the complete process. Scans a Dork, independent of a IScanProvider, parses its results, and keeps the results and the status fo this scan
GoolagScanner::ScanningDialogThe little neat and fancy animated dialogbox which shows progress while scanning
